#originalTopic=does-intelligent-design-have-merit
"First and foremost - how does an animal without an immune system survive to acquire one. "It does not acquire one... it already has one from it's ancestors.Evolution does not 'recreate' everything from scratch, it builds on previously evolved systems.  As such when an animal 'evolved' the immune system of it's ancestor evolve with it.  Evolution is not a one mutation at a time deal, it involves multiple mutations happening throughout the life form.